    1. Corky [97]September 9th, 2013
       4:34 pm
       #1
       The real injustice is the fact that tax lien holders who sell the
       foreclosed properties are not required to refund any remaining
       equity from the sale to the previous homeowner. They basically get
       to steal a house minus the taxes owed to the District. A more
       reasonable system would permit lien holders to obtain a reasonable
       profit and costs from a foreclosure, but be required to return any
       remainder to the owner. No one should be able to steal tens of
       thousands in equity to pay off a 1000 tax lien.
