       the worst instances.
       The only bad thing about this program are attorneys fees. Cap them
       at 1 or 2k.
       There is no incentive for someone to pay anothers debt if there is
       not an off chance of foreclosure. Every state in the country has
       tax liens and attached foreclosures.
       Again manage attorneys fees, make concessions for the elderly and
       handicapped in a primary residence read: not owners of vacant or
       blighted properties, and don't throw out the baby with the bath
       water
